This paper deals with the problem of classification with uncertainty quantification, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of Gaussian processes is a well-established approach in this field, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Dirichlet distribution, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach for classification, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
